-----------------------------------------------

Oneohtrix Point Never is the alias of Daniel 

Lopatin, a Brooklyn musician whose tarnished 

sci-fi yearnings are evident in his titles-- 

"Betrayed in the Octagon", "Transmat Memories", 

"Laser to Laser", "Hyperdawn"-- and in his 

penchant for sad, sourly tuned analog 

synthesizers. Oneohtrix Point Never's music is 

in love with technology but finds it 

nevertheless a source of sadness, anxiety, and 

gleaming fatigue, as well as redemption.
